                        </li>
                                              <li data-a="2">
                          inscription: mount, brown ink, upper left corner: 249 [underlined]
                        </li>
                                          
                    
                                      </ul>
                              </dd>
            
          </dl>
        </dd>
        
                  <dt>Provenance</dt>
          <dd>Charles Rogers, London (his mark, Lugt 624, black ink, lower right) sale [Thomas Philipe, London, April 20, 1799, lot 547]. Sale [Sotheby's, New York, 28 January 1998, lot 34] sold; to Jeffrey E. Horvitz, Boston, gift; to Harvard Art Museums, 2008</dd>
        
        
        
        <dt>Acquisition and Rights</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
